    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix thread-unsafe access in init_eNB_afterRU function\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_eNB_afterRU` function in `nr-gnb.c` was modifying the global `RC.nb_nr_inst` variable without proper synchronization, leading to potential race conditions when accessed by multiple threads. This could cause unpredictable behavior or crashes in multi-threaded environments.\n\nThe fix adds mutex protection around the critical section where `RC.nb_nr_inst` is modified, using the existing `RC.ru_mutex` that's already used for protecting other RC structure accesses.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-gnb.c`: Added pthread mutex locking around the modification of `RC.nb_nr_inst` when `NFAPI_MODE == NFAPI_MODE_PNF`\n- The mutex is only held for the brief time needed to modify the variable, minimizing performance impact\n\n### Reproduction\nIn a multi-threaded environment with NFAPI PNF mode enabled, concurrent access to the `init_eNB_afterRU` function could lead to:\n- Inconsistent values of `RC.nb_nr_inst` \n- Potential segmentation faults when accessing `RC.gNB` array with invalid indices\n- Unpredictable behavior in gNB initialization\n\nThe issue is most likely to manifest under high load conditions where multiple threads might attempt to initialize gNB instances concurrently.\n"
}